comments: Collins (SAS) initiates contact with Knox II's (POR) right arm, affecting his ability to control the rebound.
Minaya (POR) initiates contact with Jones's (SAS) lower body that affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Jones (SAS) dislodges the ball from Eubanks (POR) and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Champagnie (SAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Eubanks (POR) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Johnson (SAS) and incidental contact occurs as Johnson (SAS) attempts to move over the pick.

Walker (POR) makes a normal basketball move when contact occurs with Collins' (SAS) head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Knox II (POR) contests the post shot attempt by Bates-Diop (SAS) and any arm contact is marginal.
Eubanks (POR) establishes himself in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Walker (POR) makes marginal contact to Johnson's (SAS) body that he is able to move through and continue his path to the basket during his drive.
Eubanks (POR) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Johnson's (SAS) layup attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Champagnie (SAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Champagnie moves laterally into Knox II (POR) and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Eubanks (POR) commits a take foul on Bates-Diop (SAS).
Minaya (POR) commits a take foul on Jones (SAS).
